01:29:40.477 --> 01:29:42.104
Yuichi.

1443
01:29:46.942 --> 01:29:48.360
<i>I went into hiding.</i>

1444
01:29:49.278 --> 01:29:52.322
<i>I searched for a way
to strike at the White Death</i>

1445
01:29:52.406 --> 01:29:55.075
<i>without endangering what I had left.</i>

1446
01:29:55.743 --> 01:29:58.037
But he remained forever out of reach.

1447
01:29:59.747 --> 01:30:01.165
I did not think

1448
01:30:01.248 --> 01:30:04.877
fate would ever give me
a chance to make things right.

1449
01:30:06.962 --> 01:30:09.923
Do you know what they call
a ladybug in Japan?

1450
01:30:11.341 --> 01:30:12.301
Uh-uh.

1451
01:30:13.052 --> 01:30:14.219
<i>Tentoumushi.</i>

1452
01:30:14.803 --> 01:30:18.932
As a boy. I was told
there is a spot on its back

1453
01:30:19.016 --> 01:30:21.477
for each
of the seven sorrows of the world.

1454
01:30:22.478 --> 01:30:25.689
You see. <i>tentoumushi</i> is not lucky.

1455
01:30:26.231 --> 01:30:31.278
It holds all the bad luck
so that others may live in peace.

1456
01:30:34.238 --> 01:30:36.657
I don't wanna hold the seven sorrows.

1457
01:30:36.741 --> 01:30:40.703
Everything that's ever happened to you
has led you here.

1458
01:30:42.455 --> 01:30:43.498
Fate.

1459
01:30:44.123 --> 01:30:45.958
Well. that's a shit deal.

1460
01:30:47.835 --> 01:30:49.253
At Kyoto Station.

1461
01:30:50.046 --> 01:30:52.882
the White Death
will arrive on this train.

1462
01:30:53.925 --> 01:30:56.928
I will finally be allowed
to make things right.

1463
01:30:58.638 --> 01:31:00.598
My son is a few cars up.

1464
01:31:00.681 --> 01:31:03.351
If you could escort him off this train...

1465
01:31:04.393 --> 01:31:08.773
Yeah. I don't see the White Death
letting any of us off this train.

1466
01:31:10.525 --> 01:31:12.735
You let me worry
about the White Death.

1467
01:31:15.446 --> 01:31:16.280
Okay.

1468
01:31:19.450 --> 01:31:20.743
Mr. Ladybug?

1469
01:31:23.371 --> 01:31:25.873
- Your briefcase.
- Thank you.

1470
01:31:25.957 --> 01:31:27.959
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1471
01:31:34.298 --> 01:31:36.050
[KIMURA GROANING]

1472
01:31:37.718 --> 01:31:38.802
[IN JAPANESE] Father.

1473
01:31:40.637 --> 01:31:41.680
I don't understand.

1474
01:31:42.848 --> 01:31:44.683
[IN JAPANESE] It is fate. my son.

1475
01:31:45.308 --> 01:31:46.518
And Wataru?

1476
01:31:46.601 --> 01:31:47.811
He is safe.

1477
01:31:51.189 --> 01:31:52.149
Well...

1478
01:31:52.858 --> 01:31:54.401
he seemed like a decent guy.

1479
01:31:55.819 --> 01:31:56.862
[IN ENGLISH] He shot me.

1480
01:31:57.445 --> 01:31:58.405
Me. too.

1481
01:31:58.488 --> 01:31:59.364
Twice.

1482
01:32:00.282 --> 01:32:01.867
Still. he had another side to him...

1483
01:32:01.950 --> 01:32:03.076
[YAWNING]

1484
01:32:04.452 --> 01:32:05.537
Wow.

1485
01:32:09.416 --> 01:32:10.542
Oh. man.

1486
01:32:11.918 --> 01:32:13.003
Am I in hell?

1487
01:32:15.547 --> 01:32:17.549
Ah. fuck.

1488
01:32:21.678 --> 01:32:23.054
Fuckin' vest. man.

1489
01:32:24.556 --> 01:32:26.850
Oh. you drank the water.

1490
01:32:31.146 --> 01:32:32.981
Where the fuck is my brother?

1491
01:32:33.064 --> 01:32:35.066
["FIVE HUNDRED MILES" PLAYING]

1492
01:32:51.749 --> 01:32:57.171
<i>♪ If you missed the train I'm on ♪</i>

1493
01:32:57.254 --> 01:33:01.425
<i>♪ You will know that I am gone ♪</i>

1494
01:33:01.508 --> 01:33:04.136
<i>♪ You can hear ♪</i>

1495
01:33:04.220 --> 01:33:05.304
Aw. man.

1496
01:33:05.387 --> 01:33:11.227
<i>♪ The whistle blow a hundred miles ♪</i>

1497
01:33:11.310 --> 01:33:16.523
<i>♪ A hundred miles. a hundred miles ♪</i>

1498
01:33:16.607 --> 01:33:19.652
<i>♪ A hundred miles. a hundred miles ♪</i>

1499
01:33:19.735 --> 01:33:20.653
You...

1500
01:33:20.736 --> 01:33:25.783
<i>♪ You can hear the whistle blow ♪</i>

1501
01:33:25.866 --> 01:33:27.910
You were more
like Thomas anyway. right?

1502
01:33:27.993 --> 01:33:32.414
<i>♪ A hundred miles ♪</i>

1503
01:33:39.338 --> 01:33:41.674
[YELLS]

1504
01:33:41.757 --> 01:33:46.595
<i>♪ Lord. I'm one. Lord. I'm two ♪</i>

1505
01:33:46.679 --> 01:33:51.432
<i>♪ Lord. I'm three. Lord. I'm four ♪</i>

1506
01:33:51.516 --> 01:33:56.646
<i>♪ Lord. I'm five hundred miles ♪</i>

1507
01:33:56.729 --> 01:34:02.235
<i>♪ From my home... ♪</i>

1508
01:34:02.318 --> 01:34:03.528
[LADYBUG] Fellas.

1509
01:34:03.611 --> 01:34:06.030
We need to come up with a plan.

1510
01:34:06.114 --> 01:34:10.034
You killed my brother.
You killed my brother. you piece of shit!

1511
01:34:10.118 --> 01:34:12.453
Yeah. you fucking shot me!

1512
01:34:12.537 --> 01:34:14.289
I'll shoot you in the fucking throat
next time

1513
01:34:14.372 --> 01:34:16.249
and your fucking partner Keira Knightley!

1514
01:34:16.332 --> 01:34:18.293
- She is not my...
- Hey! Fellas!

1515
01:34:18.376 --> 01:34:21.462
When we are so quick to anger.
we are slow to understand.

1516
01:34:21.546 --> 01:34:23.506
I'm fast to kick your ass. though.
I swear to God.

1517
01:34:25.133 --> 01:34:28.219
Fucking piece of shit! I shoulda
put a bullet through your fucking ass!

1518
01:34:28.303 --> 01:34:30.596
When you point a finger
at someone in blame.

1519
01:34:30.680 --> 01:34:32.724
there are four fingers
pointing back at you.

1520
01:34:33.433 --> 01:34:35.685
Or three. That's weird.

1521
01:34:35.768 --> 01:34:38.062
Fuck it! That's it!
You know what I could do!

1522
01:34:38.146 --> 01:34:40.523
- We before me!
- You before fucking God...

1523
01:34:40.606 --> 01:34:41.649
Gentlemen!

1524
01:34:42.734 --> 01:34:43.735
Get off me!

1525
01:34:44.527 --> 01:34:49.782
A plum does not resent the hungry man.
but the farmer who planted the tree.

1526
01:34:51.867 --> 01:34:53.952
He resents the farmer?

1527
01:34:54.036 --> 01:34:56.872
So how do plums have fuckin' resentments?
So how can it resent?

1528
01:34:56.955 --> 01:34:59.791
Listen. The White Death is the farmer.

1529
01:35:02.085 --> 01:35:04.338
So we're the plums. We're the plums?

1530
01:35:04.421 --> 01:35:06.923
It don't make sense.
Why are you motherfuckers using metaphors?

1531
01:35:07.007 --> 01:35:08.592
Look. he shot my fucking brother!

1532
01:35:08.675 --> 01:35:10.302
You shot my son!

1533
01:35:14.348 --> 01:35:15.932
We prepare together...

1534
01:35:16.892 --> 01:35:18.435
or we die alone.

1535
01:35:20.270 --> 01:35:21.938
That's all I was trying to say.

1536
01:35:22.022 --> 01:35:24.024
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1537
01:35:25.734 --> 01:35:30.405
[ELDER] <i>The White Death waits for you
with his army of assassins.</i>

1538
01:35:30.489 --> 01:35:33.116
<i>Killers from all countries.</i>

1539
01:35:33.658 --> 01:35:39.039
<i>But he has no idea
my son and I are on this train.</i>

1540
01:35:39.581 --> 01:35:41.083
<i>If fate wills.</i>

1541
01:35:41.917 --> 01:35:43.794
<i>I will get my revenge.</i>

1542
01:35:45.379 --> 01:35:48.882
[KIMURA] <i>I'll head to the back
and stop as many as I can.</i>

1543
01:35:49.424 --> 01:35:52.969
[LEMON] <i>I'll go to the driver car
and get us the fuck out of here.</i>

1544
01:35:58.015 --> 01:36:00.643
What are you gonna do. Joburg?

1545
01:36:02.770 --> 01:36:04.146
I'm gonna buy us some time.

1546
01:36:05.189 --> 01:36:07.191
{\an8}[DRAMATIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

1547
01:37:02.287 --> 01:37:03.371
[IN RUSSIAN] Daughter.

1548
01:37:05.123 --> 01:37:06.291
[IN RUSSIAN] Father.

1549
01:37:07.000 --> 01:37:09.002
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1550
01:37:11.754 --> 01:37:14.382
[FAINT BEEPING]

1551
01:37:14.466 --> 01:37:17.385
[LADYBUG] Hey. uh. fellas.
I'm looking for a Mr. Death.

1552
01:37:17.469 --> 01:37:18.970
Got his case here.

1553
01:37:19.721 --> 01:37:21.139
Hey. easy.

1554
01:37:29.439 --> 01:37:31.065
Hurt people hurt people.

1555
01:37:38.072 --> 01:37:39.449
[IN ENGLISH] I came to see you.

1556
01:37:40.408 --> 01:37:41.493
Hm.

1557
01:37:41.576 --> 01:37:44.037
And to make you finally see me.

1558
01:37:45.955 --> 01:37:47.499
[IN RUSSIAN] The real me.

1559
01:37:49.125 --> 01:37:50.251
Hm.

1560
01:37:50.335 --> 01:37:54.047
I built myself up
from the nothing you gave me.

1561
01:37:54.130 --> 01:37:56.966
All so I could be
the one in front of you today...

1562
01:37:57.926 --> 01:37:59.511
my finger on the trigger.

1563
01:38:01.804 --> 01:38:03.348
I was the one...

1564
01:38:04.474 --> 01:38:06.391
...who deserved your attention.

1565
01:38:10.604 --> 01:38:11.772
Your love.

1566
01:38:12.773 --> 01:38:16.401
I'm more like you
than that little fuckup ever was.

1567
01:38:24.243 --> 01:38:25.661
[LAUGHS]

1568
01:38:30.541 --> 01:38:31.708
[IN ENGLISH] Do it.

1569
01:38:34.169 --> 01:38:35.587
I came here to kill you.

1570
01:38:37.965 --> 01:38:39.341
So kill me.

1571
01:38:41.677 --> 01:38:44.429
Kill me like you did
all the others who tried the same.

1572
01:38:44.513 --> 01:38:46.515
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1573
01:38:55.983 --> 01:38:57.067
Do it.

1574
01:39:03.407 --> 01:39:04.741
Fucking do it!

1575
01:39:08.537 --> 01:39:09.997
- [IMITATES GUNSHOT]
- [GASPS]

1576
01:39:10.621 --> 01:39:12.331
Pow. [LAUGHS]

1577
01:39:18.421 --> 01:39:20.047
[IN ENGLISH] I see you. <i>dochka.</i>

1578
01:39:21.299 --> 01:39:23.217
[IN RUSSIAN] I always have.

1579
01:39:25.595 --> 01:39:29.390
But you have never been part of my plan.

1580
01:39:35.438 --> 01:39:36.939
We found the American!

1581
01:39:40.026 --> 01:39:41.402
[IN ENGLISH] What about the others?

1582
01:39:41.485 --> 01:39:42.820
They're all dead.

1583
01:39:43.446 --> 01:39:46.407
Uh. good news is I have your case.

1584
01:39:47.617 --> 01:39:49.994
Ay. good news. good news.

1585
01:39:50.077 --> 01:39:51.787
[IN RUSSIAN] Check the case.

1586
01:39:51.871 --> 01:39:54.290
Hurry. Move. Let's go.

1587
01:39:55.916 --> 01:39:57.168
[WHITE DEATH] Clear the train.

1588
01:39:59.378 --> 01:40:02.882
All right. Thomas.
Time for you to start up...

1589
01:40:02.965 --> 01:40:05.468
Oh. shit. Everything's in Japanese.

1590
01:40:05.551 --> 01:40:07.470
There is no episode in Japanese.
What the f...?

1591
01:40:12.016 --> 01:40:13.309
Get on the ground!

1592
01:40:20.398 --> 01:40:24.069
Man. I got a bad feeling about this.
We have no idea what's in this case.

1593
01:40:24.152 --> 01:40:25.195
What are you talkin' about?

1594
01:40:25.278 --> 01:40:27.739
Why is it always gotta be us
that opens this shit?

1595
01:40:27.822 --> 01:40:29.491
Just open the goddamn case.

1596
01:40:29.574 --> 01:40:31.326
I'd like to keep my fuckin' arms.

1597
01:40:32.077 --> 01:40:34.454
Uh. Mr. Death. if I may?

1598
01:40:35.664 --> 01:40:37.582
The shadow buyer

1599
01:40:38.249 --> 01:40:41.878
<i>who bought all our contracts.
got us all on this train.</i>

1600
01:40:41.961 --> 01:40:42.921
<i>Me. the Hornet.</i>

1601
01:40:43.004 --> 01:40:44.506
Tangerine. Lemon...

1602
01:40:45.215 --> 01:40:46.132
[BOTH] Oh!

1603
01:40:46.216 --> 01:40:47.717
That was you. right?

1604
01:40:48.760 --> 01:40:51.012
[IN ENGLISH] Yes. very astute.

1605
01:40:51.096 --> 01:40:53.890
I brought you on this train
hoping you'd kill each other.

1606
01:40:53.973 --> 01:40:55.558
Okay. Well. um...

1607
01:40:56.935 --> 01:40:59.562
If I could... Why?

1608
01:40:59.646 --> 01:41:01.981
Why you do what you do?

1609
01:41:02.065 --> 01:41:04.776
You know. I've been
asking that very question.

1610
01:41:04.859 --> 01:41:07.237
If it's so safe.
why didn't he just open it?

1611
01:41:07.320 --> 01:41:09.698
What if it's a bomb
and it blows up in our faces?

1612
01:41:09.781 --> 01:41:12.200
You think these stupid masks
are gonna protect us?

1613
01:41:12.283 --> 01:41:14.285
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1614
01:41:17.997 --> 01:41:19.707
[ELDER IN JAPANESE]
All these years later...

1615
01:41:19.790 --> 01:41:24.211
the burden of your betrayal
still heavy upon your heads.

1616
01:41:26.547 --> 01:41:28.924
Let me relieve you of both.

1617
01:41:30.008 --> 01:41:31.301
My wife...

1618
01:41:32.678 --> 01:41:34.012
was taken from me.

1619
01:41:37.433 --> 01:41:41.812
I heard. I'm so sorry for your loss.
It was a horrible accident.

1620
01:41:43.897 --> 01:41:45.691
- Horrible.
- Oh. no.

1621
01:41:45.774 --> 01:41:49.319
No. Nothing in life is an accident.

1622
01:41:49.903 --> 01:41:52.865
It was an assassination attempt on me.

1623
01:41:52.948 --> 01:41:53.824
But fate...

1624
01:41:55.826 --> 01:41:59.204
Fate put two wet work operatives.

1625
01:41:59.788 --> 01:42:03.250
<i>twins. on a job in Bolivia.</i>

1626
01:42:04.710 --> 01:42:07.671
<i>butchering my entire crew.</i>

1627
01:42:07.755 --> 01:42:10.507
And I had to go deal with it.

1628
01:42:10.591 --> 01:42:13.010
And he didn't hire
two random operators. Lemon.

1629
01:42:13.093 --> 01:42:15.471
No. he asked for the two
responsible for the Bolivia job.

1630
01:42:15.554 --> 01:42:20.684
That is why it was my wife
in the car that night.

1631
01:42:21.268 --> 01:42:22.227
not me.

1632
01:42:22.728 --> 01:42:25.813
Fate put my wife in the hospital.

1633
01:42:26.564 --> 01:42:28.399
A piece of her rib

1634
01:42:29.275 --> 01:42:31.319
piercing her heart.

1635
01:42:33.738 --> 01:42:38.868
Only the most skilled cardiovascular
surgeon could save her life.

1636
01:42:41.245 --> 01:42:46.209
But two nights earlier.
this surgeon was poisoned.

1637
01:42:48.044 --> 01:42:49.796
[YELLING] Oh. my God!

1638
01:42:49.879 --> 01:42:53.299
- Fate. Fate again.
- [EKG FLATLINES]

1639
01:42:53.382 --> 01:42:54.884
They said my money was in the case!

1640
01:42:55.676 --> 01:42:59.347
Don't wanna sound judgmental.
but if you hired the Hornet.

1641
01:42:59.430 --> 01:43:01.599
you had your own kid killed?

1642
01:43:01.682 --> 01:43:03.392
- Oh. yes.
- Okay.

1643
01:43:03.476 --> 01:43:05.728
Oh. yes. I did. The piece of shit.

1644
01:43:06.270 --> 01:43:07.271
Please. please.

1645
01:43:07.355 --> 01:43:08.314
<i>That night...</i>

1646
01:43:09.023 --> 01:43:11.776
- Please pick me up.
<i>- ...I told her not to leave.</i>

1647
01:43:12.819 --> 01:43:14.070
<i>To wait for me.</i>

1648
01:43:14.737 --> 01:43:19.700
<i>But she promised it was the last time
we would ever bail him out of trouble.</i>

1649
01:43:19.784 --> 01:43:22.203
I will come. I will always come for you.

1650
01:43:22.870 --> 01:43:26.415
Well. I suppose she was right.

1651
01:43:27.166 --> 01:43:30.669
If I had amputated that weakness

1652
01:43:31.378 --> 01:43:33.338
out of my life years ago.

1653
01:43:33.421 --> 01:43:36.174
she would still be by my side!

1654
01:43:36.800 --> 01:43:39.928
Yeah. it helps to process this.
I have a good therapist.

1655
01:43:40.011 --> 01:43:41.888
I loved my wife very much.

1656
01:43:43.265 --> 01:43:45.141
She taught me a valuable lesson.

1657
01:43:45.809 --> 01:43:47.936
If you do not control your fate...

1658
01:43:49.271 --> 01:43:50.480
it will control you.

1659
01:43:50.564 --> 01:43:52.107
Hm. Hm?

1660
01:43:52.190 --> 01:43:54.484
So I took control.

1661
01:43:54.568 --> 01:43:56.361
I brought them all here to die.

1662
01:44:01.199 --> 01:44:04.411
<i>But now there is only one left.</i>

1663
01:44:06.580 --> 01:44:08.456
Mr. Carver.

1664
01:44:08.540 --> 01:44:10.250
Whoa. Uh...

1665
01:44:10.333 --> 01:44:11.459
Excuse me?

1666
01:44:11.543 --> 01:44:13.503
I'm filling in for Carver?
Calling in sick?

1667
01:44:13.587 --> 01:44:14.880
Fuck Carver.

1668
01:44:14.963 --> 01:44:17.424
The man who murdered my wife.

1669
01:44:17.507 --> 01:44:19.509
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1670
01:44:23.847 --> 01:44:24.681
Bro.

1671
01:44:24.764 --> 01:44:27.267
- Just open it!
- Fine. Ya happy?

1672
01:44:27.350 --> 01:44:28.184
I'm not Carver!

1673
01:44:45.284 --> 01:44:46.118
He went that way.

1674
01:44:51.123 --> 01:44:52.124
[GROANING]

1675
01:44:55.419 --> 01:44:57.046
Oh. shit. Okay.

1676
01:44:58.088 --> 01:44:59.757
Oh. shit. Something's happening.

1677
01:44:59.840 --> 01:45:01.842
["HOLDING OUT FOR A HERO" PLAYING]

1678
01:45:06.513 --> 01:45:08.140
[YELLING]

1679
01:45:28.369 --> 01:45:29.703
Excuse me.

1680
01:45:31.080 --> 01:45:32.081
Yep.

1681
01:46:13.287 --> 01:46:14.789
[WHITE DEATH IN JAPANESE] Kimura.

1682
01:46:15.623 --> 01:46:16.582
Why are you here?

1683
01:46:17.542 --> 01:46:18.751
[IN JAPANESE] Your daughter.

1684
01:46:18.835 --> 01:46:20.712
It would seem she pushed...

1685
01:46:20.795 --> 01:46:23.464
the wrong grandson off a roof.

1686
01:46:27.135 --> 01:46:30.513
[IN ENGLISH] Ah. children. You do
the best you can to raise them right.

1687
01:46:32.306 --> 01:46:34.142
Cockroach.
I do not know why you are here.

